5:
This is where they were last spotted,
yeah? These... imposter Crimson
Blades that are running around
pillaging ships.
9:
Indeed. It's almost impressive that
they were brave enough to claim
the name without fearing HER
wrath...
12:
By the way, Liao, thank you for
letting us borrow your ship. I'm sorry
we had to trouble you with this.
16:
Don't be. With how much we travel,
we'd eventually run into these
pirates anyway. Better to mop them
up now than later.
20:
Speaking of, I can see a suspicious
ship on the horizon. Get ready.
24:
Heh, looks like our next target is
gonna be full of booty!
26:
We'll sink any sucker who crosses us
Crimson Blades!
29: N-no way... Those two can't be...
35:
The slender one's shoulders are too
narrow, and he has a hunched back.
The larger one is too obese. These
two are a far cry from their real
counterparts.
39:
They're getting ready to attack. We
should begin battle preparations.
42:
Aye, aye, Captain. It's time to show
Alk and Light our true capabilities on
the high seas!
44:
We're coming up within boarding
distance! Alk, Light, take care of our
captain!
50:
I'm far too old for cat sitters.
Let's go.
56:
Not on my watch! Is this really how
you think a Crimson Blade would act?
58:
Shaddup! So what if we stole the
name? They ain't here no more, so
what's it to you?
61:
I believe I'm beginning to see what
happened. Was it revenge or
jealousy?
64:
Your appearances bear no signs of
cosmetic surgery, meaning... Other
people would've surely mistook you
both for the real Crimson Blades.
69:
Give it up. Drop this act. So long as
you're alive, you can still turn your
life around.
74: Wh-what was that?! A tidal wave?
99:
I'm completely fine, but this man
needs immediate medical attention.
102:
...He's in cardiac arrest. Guard me
while I perform CPR!
107:
We'll buy you as much time as you
need!
110:
Why are you helping him? We tried
to kill you.
113:
So what if you did? The Fellowship of
Floof provides treatment to anyone
and everyone, regardless of who
they are!
116:
We'll keep going until the day these
ocean waters are free of pain and
suffering! Call it a pipe dream if you
want—
118:
I'll never stop trying to make that
ideal a reality!
121:
...Take care of him. Don't let him die,
aye?
123:
All hands on deck, ready your
weapons! It's squid hunting time!
127:
Of course I won't. He'll be right as
rain by the time I'm done with him!
132: Guess I owe you my damn life.
134:
A debt which you'll repay. Here's
your bill. We accept payment in the
form of labor if you're short on
money.
137:
Ain't no way you seriously expected
me to be able to pay this.
139:
But you know what? This might be
the perfect opportunity to change
careers.
141:
...We always wanted to be like the
Crimson Blades. But we never had
anyone like Marina to show us the
ropes.
143:
Our crew looked up to the legends
she left behind. We just wanted to
be like her, as much as we could.
145:
You say that like you've already
given up on being legends
yourselves. I say that it's not too late.
148:
I'm starting to think working under
you might not be so bad. You have
our blades, Cap'n.
151:
Welcome to the crew.
Now that you're officially in...
154:
Please put those on. Our first and
foremost rule is that you have to
wear those ears at all times.
165:
Hey, Liao. You should tell me more
stories about when you were
younger.
168:
Or give me more details about this
ideal world you wanna create. I
want to know more about you.
172:
I don't mind sharing. I assume you'd
like to hear more about my
residency?
175:
You know, I had a classmate who
used to be a member of the clergy—
